<h3>Resource Bank</h3><p>
From the October Edition of <i>The Insider</i><br>
<h2>New Heritage Publications</h2></center>
<P>
<HR>
<B>Backgrounder</B>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><a href=""> Needed: A Congressional Freedom of Information Act (No. 1098)</a>
<LI><a href="/heritage/library/categories/crimelaw/bg1097.html">	How State and Local Officials Can Combat Violent Juvenile Crime (No. 1097) </a>
<LI><a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bg1096.html">	Rethinking the Bosnia Bargain (No. 1096) </a>
<LI><a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1095.html">	Re-invention Has Not Ended the "Era of Big Government" (No. 1095) </a>
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<B>Backgrounder Update</B>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bgup282.html"> Setting the Record Straight on Haiti (No. 282) </a>
<LI><a href="/heritage/library/categories/govern/bgup281.html">	LIUNA, Organized Crime, and the Clinton Administration (No. 281) </a>
</UL>
