Exchange Council (ALEC) will cosponsor a conference on state welfare
reform at the Renaissance Washington Hotel in Washington, DC.
This day-long conference will assemble hundreds of state legislators,
executive branch officials, and think tank and business leaders
from across the country to discuss policy ideas for states to
manage the devolution of welfare. Invited speakers include Connecticut
Governor John Rowland, U.S. Representatives James Talent and J.
C. Watts, California Social Services Director Eloise Anderson,
Wisconsin Welfare Replacement Initiative Project Director Jason
Turner, Texas Policy Director Vance McMahan, Heritage Senior Policy
Analyst Robert Rector, American Institute for Full Employment
Executive Director Theodore Abram, and <I>Tragedy of American
Compassion</I> author Marvin Olasky. The conference immediately
precedes the ALEC National Orientation Conference in the same
hotel. CONTACT: Nicole Brungard, The Heritage Foundation, 214
Massachusetts Avenue, N.E., Washington, D.C. 20002-4999, 202/608-6056,
fax 202/544-0961, e-mail <a href="mailto:Insider@heritage.org">Insider@heritage.org, </a>Internet <a href="http://www.heritage.org">http://www.heritage.org.</a><hr>

