<p><hr><p>
<b>The Family, Civil Society, and the State</b><br>
Washington, D.C.: June 21-22<p>
The American Public Philosophy Foundation will sponsor this conference to be held at the Sheraton City Centre Hotel in Washington, D.C.. Speakers will include: Michael Medved, Mary Ann Glendon, Hadley Arkes, and Robert Casey. Session topics include: "How is the current situation of the family distinctive?"; "Men and women in the family today"; "Law, divorce and family"; "Market, church, and family"; "Welfare and family"; and "What can public policy do for the family?" CONTACT: The American Public Philosophy Foundation, 414/288-6841, fax 414/288-3360.
<p><hr><p>
<b>Hillsdale College Summer Hostel Programs: Exploring the Roots of Our Liberty</b><br>
Hillsdale College: June 23-29, July 7-13, July 28-August 3<p>
Hillsdale Hostel is a week long learning vacation for seniors. The topic of this summer's hostels will be "exploring the roots of our liberty." Hillsdale Hostel explores the basic precepts underlying the American system of constitutional government and focuses on restoring America's enduring values and virtues. The sessions will be conducted by three Hillsdale professors: Dr. John Wilson, Salvatori Professor of History and Traditional Values; Dr. Daniel James Sundahl, Professor of English; and Richard Ebeling, Ludwig von Mises Professor of Economics. CONTACT: Sandi Henry, Hillsdale Hostel, Hillsdale College, 33 E. College, Hillsdale, MI 49242-9986, 800/334-8904.
<p><hr><p>
<b>American Legislative Exchange Council</b><br>
Newport, Rhode Island: July 31 to August 4<p>
ALEC will hold their Annual Meeting for free market and limited government legislators and policy makers from around the country July 31 to August 4th at the Doubletree Hotel in Newport, Rhode Island. CONTACT: American Legislative Exchange Council, 910 17th Street, N.W., Fifth Floor, Washington, D.C. 20006, 202/759-3434, fax 202/466-3801.<p><hr><p>

<b>State Policy Network's Fourth Annual Meeting</b><br>
Minneapolis, MN: September 20, 21<p>
This year's meeting will be held at the Radisson Plaza Hotel in downtown Minneapolis. CONTACT: State Policy Network, 816 Mill Lake Road, Fort Wayne, IN 46845, 219/637-7778, fax 219/637-7779.<p>
